main event: On October 30, 1966, two round objects were sighted in Centerport, Long Island, New York.
interesting points: The observer noted the objects were twinkling and appeared suddenly,The objects were stationary for about 45 seconds before disappearing,The objects were described as the size of a silver dollar and whitish-gray in color,The sighting was classified as a civilian source and deemed unreliable,The observer indicated they had seen several alleged UFOs previously.
witness description: Observer named Greenlantz, additional details redacted
